9 NEW SECTION. Section 8. Penalties. The following penalties apply to violations of this chapter:
10 (1) A retailer, wholesaler, or importer who sells or offers for sale a vapor product containing
11 nicotine for retail sale in this state or to a consumer in this state that is not included in the directory shall be
12 subject to a civil penalty of $250 for each individual vapor product containing nicotine offered for sale in
13 violation of this chapter.
14 (a) For a second violation of this type within a 12-month period, the civil penalty is $500 for each
15 individual vapor product containing nicotine offered for sale in violation of this chapter and a licensee's license
16 must be suspended for 1 month.
17 (b) For a third violation of this type within a 12-month period, the civil penalty is $750 for each
18 individual vapor product containing nicotine offered for sale in violation of this chapter and a licensee's license
19 must be suspended for 3 months.
20 (c) For a fourth or subsequent violation of this type within a 12-month period, the civil penalty is
21 $1,000 for each individual vapor product containing nicotine offered for sale in violation of this chapter and a
22 licensee's license must be suspended for 1 year.
23 (2) A vapor product manufacturer whose vapor products containing nicotine are not listed in the
24 directory and who causes the vapor products containing nicotine that are not listed to be sold for retail sale in
25 this state or to a consumer in this state, whether directly or through a retailer, wholesaler, importer, or similar
26 intermediary or intermediaries, is subject to a civil penalty of $10,000 for each individual vapor product
27 containing nicotine offered for sale in violation of this chapter. In addition, any vapor product manufacturer that
